cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.NE, cs.MM

The paper proposes a new module for object detection, which is a common task in computer vision (cs.CV). The module is designed to improve the accuracy and efficiency of a one-stage detector, which involves machine learning and optimization techniques (cs.LG). The module also involves a propose-and-attend mechanism, which is a form of attention mechanism commonly used in deep learning (cs.AI). The paper also mentions the use of lightweight backbones and train-from-scratch methods, which are topics related to neural networks and optimization (cs.NE) and multimedia (cs.MM).
